shields take alot of points to get good at. The game 'concept' wasnt all that<br>
offensive so I tried a couple times to go to Midgard and find something<br>
to kill but we all died to invisible 'snow demons?' I assume goblins or some such.<br>
Never saw any other players.<br>
<br>
See I have always wanted to see a game that at least attempted to mirror<br>
reality, and the reality is that warriors would use a shield until it became<br>
an impediment to combat. The 'dual' wield combat styles you see in so many<br>
fantasy games, are just that, 'fantasy'. Sure in Italy in the 13hundreds<br>
they had a dueling style with main-guache but it was never that popular.<br>
<br>
Again I thank you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarueivywood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darue Ivywood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 459<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/7/02 9:55:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think the end game is going to suck even more-so in the near future unless Mythic can stop hacks and cheats from ruining what little RvR experience there is.<br>
<br>
Gear: Yes, you will get banned for using this, BUT, if your smart you wont jack the speed up to 3x the speed of sprint with a speed spell(which is where it defaults to when loaded) . Doing that is asking to get caught. You can however, lower the speed to around the sprint speed and get away clean.<br>
<br>
Odins Eye: Granted it takes a second pc with a linux OS to use, but it will give the ability to see stealthed players.(as well as what is seen with DAoC Unleashed) I know what Mythic has said about this, and they are wrong. Get a stealth class (one that is intended to see through stealth) and use that class, and you will see what I mean.<br>
<br>
DAoC unleashed: this will be the kicker. Easy to use, runs on the same system and overlays the DAoC screen. can tell you everything about anyone in the field of view of the program, from HP's, class, level, distance etc(kinda a ShowEQ). The field of view is greater than the Field of view of a player due to packets sent(want to see whats on the otherside of the wall without going to the other side? this is the program for you). The only thing DAoC cannot do (as of yet) is see stealthed players.<br>
<br>
Anytime there are cheats and hacks in a player vs. player enviroment, it ruins the fun for those that dont want to use such programs. Diablo anyone?<br>
